 </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/uathathehealer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>athathehealer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>QHills and Clueless</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#628CBC>(9/25/02 3:51:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Zordak in Sol</span><hr size=1> Thanks ta me guild and especially me hubby Brutuz after 19 hours I did my pearl turn in. Here is the thing...... <br>
<br>
1.  We (some guildmates, myself and Brutuz) headed ta Sol B about 230 am EST. Cleared all the giants and waited fer repops. My hubby and I stayed through the quiet part, and then started ta clear the next set when we died.... (thank ye ta Tanilie who rezzed us both and waited fer us ta be ready ta defend the camp before makin her way out, instead of jest claimin the camp.) Called in fer some help from the guild and cleared the second set of giants. Started ta clear the third set of giants as well when other folks started ta pop in from all over.<br>
<br>
2. There were quite a few camp checks, and clerics that popped in over the course of our stay there. Throughout most of the 19 hours, the clerics who came in wished us luck and asked fer a /tell with Zordak's spawn time.<br>
<br>
3. Only one cleric claimed that it was a FFA mob and insisted that they were going to try ta do the turn in, after all the time we had spent there.  My guild came out enmasse ta support and assist. The turn in was done as quickly as possible and I recieved my swirling pearl.<br>
<br>
I am uncertain of all the guilds the clerics belonged to, however there is one cleric who arrived about halfway through my camp and remained there the entire time. When the time came close fer Zordak ta spawn and the other cleric popped in, he stated clearly that he was not goin ta participate in such a fashion and would quietly wait ta claim the camp when the turn in was complete. This cleric was Amsterdam from LoV. Many thanks ta ye fer remainin true ta the Morrell Thule play nice policy. <br>
<br>
To all the clerics out there waiting their turn fer this mob, I wish ye all the best. Although this is now the bottle neck of our epic, with folks out there that remember the general politness and comradarie we here on MT show one another, this camp should not be a nightmare.If done properly, ye would have ta spend no more then 24 or so hours at the camp, (yes exhaustion does set in /giggle) and a cleric will be epified every day on MT.<br>
